---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout title="About Us | SIMG">
  <Header slot="header" />
  <main>
    <h1>About SIMG Seminar</h1>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Una Comunidad de Cientificos y equipos multifaceticos, comprometidos con la investigación y desarrollo del ecosistema de inteligencia artificial en Colombia</h2>
      <p>
        The SIMG ( Semillero de Investigación en Modelos Generativos )  aims to create 
        formation and introduction to the research group, focusing solely on
        research processes. This group will cover the following topics:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Intro to Natural Language Processing (NLP)</li>
        <li>LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)</li>
        <li>Transformers</li>
        <li>Agents</li>
        <li>Benchmarks and Fine-tuning</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Friday Classes (2:00 PM - 4:00 PM)</h2>
      <p>Our Friday sessions are dedicated to in-depth exploration of key topics:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Embeddings</li>
        <li>Transformers (e.g., building a transformer together)</li>
        <li>
          Addressing a single, particular topic that is correlated with other
          subjects.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Content for 2025-2</h2>
      <h3>Introduction to Generative Models</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Why Deep Generative Modeling</li>
        <li>Probabilistic Models</li>
        <li>Autoregressive Models (Transformers)</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Essential for Diffusion Models</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Flow-Based Models</li>
        <li>Latent Variable Models</li>
        <li>Energy-Based Models</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Professional Practice</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>PyTorch for Research</li>
        <li>Fine-tuning</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

